A lost opportunity.

column35: Open office layouts have proved to be detrimental to productivity -- particularly for the engineering work that we do as a firm. I find it extremely difficult to concentrate (people are always telling me random things just because they can due to lack of partitioning-- "I'm tired today" "this water tastes bad" "can you water the plants?") and I have had to invest in noise cancelling headphones to focus and visually remind people that I'm here to do work.
